      "text": "The proposed platform solves a key student coordination challenge by matching domain expertise in project planning. It targets active college students seeking partners for hackathons, group work, or mutual study.\n\nTo build this in 2 weeks, we leverage Next.js for client-side state alongside a Python FastAPI service hosting the match rules, persisted via Supabase PostgreSQL, and secured with Clerk authenticate. Deployment happens rapidly on Vercel and Render.\n\nKey risks include cold start engagement barriers and trust verification. By phasing milestones from auth (Week 1) through logic (Week 2), chatting (Week 3), and testing (Week 4), the application is fully ready for student validation."
